      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "67735283bdda1cd5",
      "text": "Clicking any of the possible choices shows a thumb-up or a thumb-down glyph, and the given description for the choice."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "8bbd836c352db269",
      "text": "The stem and the choice/description are presented on the MCQ data paragraph as one line.  Linefeed means new data line.  Data lines are presented with a letter, ': ', text of stem/answer/question, and optionally '; ' followed with the description of the choice.  The description should repeat the choice in some form, as the choice is hidden when the description is shown.  There should be five lines in each MCQ paragraph."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "b8a9a54dcfdbdb9b",
      "text": "When a choice is clicked, the description is shown.  User can then click any other choice, there's no constraints on this, but also the old choices are not redisplayed, but the description stays visible.  To see the choices again the user should refresh the page."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "abe19c6d420daed7",
      "text": "Currently, no data is saved by this plugin, so there's no records of progress of the user.  Adding a supermemo/anki algorithm to this MCQ would be nice."
